                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11 G 93/1190: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-22T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 22, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Minister from Ecuador asked August 19th that Guayaquil and Quito Railway
                    matter be submitted to arbitration in accordance with Article 27 of the
                    contract. In view of statements made in your despatch No. 701, July 28,
                    Department was hopeful prospects of amicable settlement would make this
                    unnecessary. Investigate and cable brief statement situation with
                    recommendations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
